This paper deals with learning probabilistic models for partial ranking using crowdsourced data. The paper proposes a novel framework for margin-based Maximum Likelihood Estimate (MLE) method, which is a popular technique in machine learning and falls under the category of supervised learning. The paper also discusses three generalized linear models, which are commonly used in machine learning and statistics. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), and cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction).
